{"article_id":"f7eicB9QU3kzpohN","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Virtually everyone agrees","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"that allowing the nation to fall off the fiscal cliff would be a bad thing .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"Government programs would be cut ,","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"taxes would rise significantly on a majority of Americans ,","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"and","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"according to the Congressional Budget Office ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"the economy would fall back into recession .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"But get this :","depth":3},{"id":8,"text":"Even if all of those things happen ,","depth":4},{"id":9,"text":"there would still be a budget deficit .","depth":4},{"id":10,"text":"When it comes to describing the fiscal cliff","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"- that combination of tax increases and spending cuts","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"that would automatically begin in January","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"unless Congress and the president step in -","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"federal budget guru Stan Collender turns to superlatives .","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"Expiration of tax cuts","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"that were started under President George W. Bush","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"`` would clearly constitute one of the biggest tax increases","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"ever imposed on taxpayers in American history , ''","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"says Collender ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"who works at Qorvis Communications .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"According to one analysis ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"ending the Bush-era tax cuts would cost the average household $ 3,500 a year .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"And then there 's the other side of the fiscal cliff :","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"what 's known as sequestration -","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"about $ 110 billion in automatic across-the-board spending cuts","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"that would hit everything from schools to weapons systems every year for the next decade .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"`` That would be the single largest one-year reduction , nominal reduction , in the deficit in American history , ''","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"says Collender .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"This would take a significant bite out of what would be a $ 1 trillion deficit .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"Still , the government would spend more","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"than it takes in .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"The Congressional Budget Office projects a $ 641 billion budget deficit for the fiscal year","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"that started Oct. 1","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"- and that 's","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"assuming","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"the fiscal cliff actually happens","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"and is in effect for three-fourths of the fiscal year .","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"It 's `` a big , big , big , big , big number , ''","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"says Maya MacGuineas , president of the Committee for a Responsible Federal Budget .","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"But here 's the thing","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"you 'd be hard-pressed to find a politician or economist or even deficit hawk like MacGuineas","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"who thinks","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"letting the nation go over the fiscal cliff is a good idea .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"`` It 's true that it 's done in the absolute wrong way ,","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"but it 's still not even big enough","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"to start to tackle the fiscal problems","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"that we have , ''","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"MacGuineas says .","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"Now let 's imagine","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"Congress wants to extend the tax cuts :","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"You can add nearly $ 250 billion to the deficit for this fiscal year .","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"Do that for a decade","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"and it will add more than $ 5 trillion in debt .","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"You might be thinking","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"this could be solved","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"by letting taxes go up on those","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"making more than $ 250,000 per year .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"Think again .","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"That only shaves about 20 percent off the bill .","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"Avoid the painful cuts of the sequester","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"- you can add more than $ 1 trillion to the debt over the next 10 years .","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"And now you 're talking about a big , big , big , big , big number .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":127,"left":73,"right":126,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":73,"left":70,"right":72,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":70,"left":65,"right":69,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":65,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":69,"left":2,"right":68,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":68,"left":3,"right":67,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":67,"left":4,"right":66,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":66,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":72,"left":7,"right":71,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":71,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":126,"left":112,"right":125,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":112,"left":94,"right":111,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":77,"right":93,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":77,"left":76,"right":14,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":76,"left":10,"right":75,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":75,"left":11,"right":74,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":74,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":8